text: Annie Lazor (born August 17, 1994) is an American competitive swimmer. In 2019, she represented the United States at the 2019 Pan American Games held in Lima, Peru. She won the gold medal in the women's 100 metre breaststroke and women's 200 metre breaststroke events.
